[DhtmlXQ_comment0]op ldz c2 65 57c vs sch3pa ||第65局五七炮对屏风马3卒 ||||ECCO：C06 中炮左邊馬對屏風馬||ECCO：C06 Central Cannon with Left Side Horse Variation vs Screen Horse Defense.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment4]As seen from the diagram, red plays the 3 pawn before red has a chance to choose which pawn to advance.||This is the basic starting formation of an age old opening, and could be seen in the Qing Dynasty's Plum Flower Manual.||As black has advanced the pawn too early, his intentions are clear and red would have an easy time countering.||Red would also develop his pieces faster than black and would let black lag further behind in the opening.||That is why it is seldom played nowadays.||But it still has its followers and can be still seen now and then in major competitions.。[/DhtmlXQ_comment4]
